title: Xenon isotopes` cross sections in reactions of high-energy protons with Ba, REE, Ta, W and Re

x4codes.hlp: Institute for High Energy Physics, Protvino, Russia

x4freetext: Targets were specially welded glasses with 10% of Ba or
REE. Ta, W, Re foils of 200 mg/cm2 thickness.
Thin glasses (0.6 - 0.8 mm) were used at Ep= 25, 50 MeV
Thick glasses (1. - 2. mm) were used at Ep= 30, 70 GeV
